        "Title": "Revit Parameter Writer",
        "DescriptionText": "Param Writer + Config\nOpens a dialog on run where you select which connector families to move and which to update — independently. For selected Move families, repositions each connector onto its parent Data Cube, evenly spaced along the cube's longest axis. For selected Update families, reads the UM-Revit Mapping sheet directly from the Utility Matrix Excel file to determine which parameters apply to which family, then writes values from the Excel data to matched Revit elements keyed by Connection ID. If a parameter is read-only (type parameter), it finds and swaps to the matching family type instead of writing directly. Config supplies the Revit categories to collect from and the key parameter (Connection ID).",
